Note:
C# Comprehensive Test Suite Runner

Runs all C# test suites:
1. Parser tests (10 tests)
2. HIR translation tests (10 tests)
3. Round-trip translation tests (30+ tests)

Total: 50+ comprehensive tests
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

@Reasoning:
Aggregated four-counter struct for the C# suite-of-suites driver.
Tracks whole suites (parser, HIR translation, round-trip) rather
than individual tests so a single failing test doesn't get diluted
by passing peers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total_suites at 0, passed_suites at 8, failed_suites at 16,
total_tests at 24. Mutated via Layout.memory_set_integer because the
struct is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "SuiteResults":
    total_suites as Integer
    passed_suites as Integer
    failed_suites as Integer
    total_tests as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Top-level orchestrator for the C# suite-of-suites. Three sub-suite
drivers (parser, HIR translation, round-trip) cover the full
pipeline. The breakdown means a CI failure immediately diagnoses
which phase regressed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Initialize SuiteResults, print banner, then for each sub-suite:
print separator, call run_<phase>_tests, pass its return through
update_results. Final summary, return 1 on any failure.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All 3 sub-suites return 0 -> exit 0
- Any sub-suite returns non-zero -> exit 1
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type SuiteResults with
        total_suites as 0,
        passed_suites as 0,
        failed_suites as 0,
        total_tests as 0

    proc print_main_header

    Note: Run parser test suite
    proc print_suite_separator
    Let parser_result be proc run_parser_tests
    proc update_results with results, parser_result, "Parser"

    Note: Run HIR translation test suite
    proc print_suite_separator
    Let hir_result be proc run_hir_tests
    proc update_results with results, hir_result, "HIR Translation"

    Note: Run round-trip test suite
    proc print_suite_separator
    Let roundtrip_result be proc run_roundtrip_tests
    proc update_results with results, roundtrip_result, "Round-Trip"

    proc print_suite_separator
    proc print_final_results with results

    If results.failed_suites is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatcher for the C# parser suite. Integration hook for the test
harness — currently returns 0 unconditionally because the actual
parser tests live in test_csharp_parser.runa, which is invoked by
the build system rather than imported here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Display "Running C# parser tests...", then return 0. Future
integration will replace the body with an exec of test_csharp_parser.runa.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Current: always returns 0 (suite passed)
- Future: invokes test_csharp_parser.runa and forwards its exit code
@End TestCases

Process called "run_parser_tests" returns Integer:
    Note: Execute the parser test suite
    Note: Import and run test_csharp_parser module
    Display "Running C# parser tests..."
    Let result be 0
    Note: Test infrastructure will execute test_csharp_parser.runa
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatcher for the C# AST -> HIR translation suite. Integration hook
for test_csharp_to_hir.runa.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Display message, return 0. Future integration replaces the body
with an exec of test_csharp_to_hir.runa.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Current: always returns 0
- Future: invokes test_csharp_to_hir.runa and forwards its exit code
@End TestCases

Process called "run_hir_tests" returns Integer:
    Note: Execute the HIR translation test suite
    Note: Import and run test_csharp_to_hir module
    Display "Running C# HIR translation tests..."
    Let result be 0
    Note: Test infrastructure will execute test_csharp_to_hir.runa
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatcher for the C# round-trip suite. Integration hook for
test_csharp_round_trip.runa.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Display message, return 0. Future integration replaces the body
with an exec of test_csharp_round_trip.runa.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Current: always returns 0
- Future: invokes test_csharp_round_trip.runa and forwards its exit code
@End TestCases

Process called "run_roundtrip_tests" returns Integer:
    Note: Execute the round-trip test suite
    Note: Import and run test_csharp_round_trip module
    Display "Running C# round-trip tests..."
    Let result be 0
    Note: Test infrastructure will execute test_csharp_round_trip.runa
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Updates SuiteResults counters and prints per-suite pass/fail line.
Centralized so all three run_*_tests calls feed through one
bookkeeping path.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. Read total_suites at offset 0; write +1.
2. If suite_result == 0 (pass): read passed_suites at 8, write +1,
   print "[SUITE PASSED] <name>".
3. Otherwise: read failed_suites at 16, write +1, print
   "[SUITE FAILED] <name>".
@End Implementation

Process called "update_results" takes results as Integer, suite_result as Integer, suite_name as String returns Integer:
    Let total be proc memory_get_integer with results, 0
    proc memory_set_integer with results, 0, total plus 1

    If suite_result is equal to 0:
        Let passed be proc memory_get_integer with results, 8
        proc memory_set_integer with results, 8, passed plus 1
        proc print_suite_success with suite_name
    Otherwise:
        Let failed be proc memory_get_integer with results, 16
        proc memory_set_integer with results, 16, failed plus 1
        proc print_suite_failure with suite_name
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verbose suite banner. Beyond title and "=" rule, prints a list of the
three sub-suites with expected test counts (10/10/30+) so a CI
consumer sees the work plan before any tests execute.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate and print title, "=" separator (28 chars), info intro,
then three "- <suite> (count)" labels. Each string deallocated
after print.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_main_header" returns Integer:
    Display "C# COMPREHENSIVE TEST SUITE"
    Display "============================"
    Display "Testing all C# language features:"
    Display "- Parser (10 tests)"
    Display "- HIR Translation (10 tests)"
    Display "- Round-Trip (30+ tests)"
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Visual separator between sub-suite runs. Width (28 "-") matches
the main banner so the visual structure is consistent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Print empty line via empty string, then print 28-character "-" rule.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_suite_separator" returns Integer:
    Display ""
    Display "----------------------------"
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[SUITE PASSED] <name>" line. Distinct from per-test [PASS] so a
CI grep can separate suite-level from test-level wins.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[SUITE PASSED] " prefix, print prefix and caller-owned
suite_name, deallocate the prefix.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_suite_success" takes suite_name as String returns Integer:
    Display "[SUITE PASSED] "
    Display suite_name
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[SUITE FAILED] <name>" line. Distinct from per-test [FAIL] so CI
consumers can immediately see which C# phase regressed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[SUITE FAILED] " prefix, print prefix and caller-owned
suite_name, deallocate the prefix.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_suite_failure" takes suite_name as String returns Integer:
    Display "[SUITE FAILED] "
    Display suite_name
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Suite-of-suites final summary. Single human-readable verdict
("ALL TESTS PASSED!" or "SOME TESTS FAILED!") at the end of the
log regardless of how many sub-suites ran.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Display "=" header, "FINAL RESULTS:" heading, three counter lines
(Total/Passed/Failed Suites via Display on the struct fields), then a
conditional verdict line based on failed_suites == 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_final_results" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Display "============================"
    Display "FINAL RESULTS:"

    Display "Total Suites: "
    Display results.total_suites

    Display "Passed Suites: "
    Display results.passed_suites

    Display "Failed Suites: "
    Display results.failed_suites

    If results.failed_suites is equal to 0:
        Display "ALL TESTS PASSED!"
    Otherwise:
        Display "SOME TESTS FAILED!"
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: End of C# Comprehensive Test Suite Runner
